About E4C and its games
1. What is E4C? What does it stand for?
E4C is a Web3 gaming metaverse with a multi-game delivery pipeline. With the vision to seamlessly bridge millions of Web2 players to Web3, E4C provides players with a revolutionary high-intensive, strategy-focused team fight and E-sports-integrated gameplay experience. The lore is set in the year 2100, when the temperature rises by 4 degrees with ongoing disasters and riots, almost driving mankind to extinction. Awakened Rangers are determined to save the world and human civilization.
鈥淓4C鈥 stands for 鈥淓arth 4 degrees Celsius warmer鈥, referring to a dystopian future where Earth almost becomes uninhabitable from global warming. This is a short summary of our background setting of the game and a preview of the extensive gaming metaverse.
2. What is Savior?
The name Savior was raised by Ambrus and finalized by the E4C community in 2023 as a title of all E4C community members.
The year is 2100 and temperatures have risen by 4掳C as a result of environmental deterioration.
Rangers are struggling to stay alive on the remaining continent and striving to find a piece of unpolluted land.
Now, they are calling for all Saviors to join their journey to salvation.
So, Saviors, would you like to join us and save the world?
3. What's the team behind E4C?
E4C is initiated, developed, and operated by Ambrus Studio.

4. What are the vision and mission of E4C?
- Vision: A player experience-focused game that brings 10Mn players to seamlessly transition from Web2 to Web3.
- Mission: Create a good game for a good cause.

5. Brief me on the games of E4C
E4C delivers a multi-game matrix. Up to now, E4C has one game launched and two in the development pipeline. Titles, genres and development status of E4C games are as follows:
- E4C: Fallen Arena is a multiplayer brawl game that launched in September 2022 as a gift to the community. It is now available to download and play on the E4C website and Steam.
- E4C: Final Salvation is a 3v3 mobile MOBA with an innovative gameplay loop that enables players to dominate their matches. The game will be launched at the end of 2023.
- Project LW is a fast-paced team battle game that gives players a more intense fighting experience. The game will be launched in Q2~Q3 of 2023.

6. What is E4C: Fallen Arena?
(E4C)Fallen Arena is a PC-based multiplayer brawl game launched by Ambrus Studio and was officially online on Steam in September 2022. It is considered a mysterious present to the E4C community to appreciate their support all the time. You can download the game on our official website. Players can log in either through e-mail or wallet. Both 1 vs 1 individual fights and 3 vs 3 team fights are supported. Almost every week, Ambrus will organize tournaments in Fallen Arena for all saviors to have fun and win numerous rewards.

7. What is E4C: Final Salvation?
E4C: Final Salvation is a revolutionary 3v3 mobile MOBA game and will be the base of our metaverse. It's a truly Free-to-play game without Pay-to-win and leverages Esports elements. It will revolutionize MOBA gameplay with a faster, more intensive fighting experience. It will give players more highlights to enjoy and develop tools to create, creating an open metaverse for co-creation. And it couples a unique worldview for climate actions to share the unique responsibility and mission: good game for a good cause.

8. What are the design principles of E4C games?
E4C games are developed with the same principles that aim to ensure and enhance players' experience
- Player experience above everything.
  - The recipe for the high DAU game is high-quality gameplay and a balanced, competitive experience for our players. No pay-for-power.
  - Equalize the gameplay experience of Web 2.0 and Web3 players. No threshold such as connecting the wallet.
  - Friendly to free players by deploying free-to-play and play-for-fun game economics.
  - Leverage E-sports to enhance players鈥 experience, with a competitive gameplay loop and more highlights during the match.
- Long-term sustainable game economics:
  - No grinding in the game: There are no play-to-earn systems in E4C games.
  - Sustainable and scalable Tokenomics: The Tokenomics is designed to adapt to E4C games and the extensive gaming metaverse 鈥淓4Cverse鈥 in the long run to incentivize decentralized ownership as well as keep a sustainable game economy(know more about the E4C Tokenomics).
About Ambrus Studio
9. What is Ambrus Studio?
Ambrus Studio is an impact-driven studio that makes good games for a good cause 鈥 a unique mission toward climate change.
"Ambrus" stands for "immortal" in Greek, which means we want to build lasting games and a lasting
universe, keeping lasting relationships with our players.

10. What's the team of Ambrus Studio?
Ambrus Studio is founded by the ex-CEO of Riot Games APAC, Johnson Yeh, who is also known as 鈥渢he Godfather of E-sports in China鈥 for making LoL China the largest E-sports league. The team behind E4C is Ambrus Studio, of which the core members assembled from Timi Studio of Tencent (Honor of Kings), Bytedance, RED, and other top enterprises. The team is 100% doxxed and you can go through everyone鈥檚 background on Ambrus鈥 website.

11. Who is Johnson Yeh? /Who is the founder of Ambrus Studio and E4C?
Motivated by the passion for building a good game for a good cause, Johnson founded Ambrus Studio and established the project E4C at the end of 2021. Prior to this entrepreneurship, Johnson was most known as "the Godfather of Esports in Asia" during his stay at Riot Games as the Managing Director of APAC, for he made the LPL (League of Legends Pro League in China) the most viewed and most commercially successful Esports league in the world. At the same time, he had a seat on the game development committee which launched a series of new games in Riot.
Johnson has a complex background combining scholarship, strategic consulting, gaming and Esports. He graduated from the University of Chicago and became the youngest visiting scholar at Harvard Law School at the age of 21. Later he finished his MBA at Fuqua School of Business, Duke University, and received his full-time PhD at Guanghua School of Management, Peking University. After working at McKinsey for 8 years, he turned to the gaming industry to work at the HK office of Riot Games. The combined experiences give Johnson a sharp mind with deep-dive insights and strong connections to the gaming industry. 

12. What are the roles of E4C Ambassadors, E4C Guardians, and E4C Commanders?
E4C Ambassadors are close and loyal fans of E4Cverse. They can represent the E4C community to look for potential collaborations and be invited to attend some special events. E4C Ambassadors will help with the publicity of our project and enjoy unique benefits when making great contributions. If you want to apply for the ambassador, plz fill in this form: https://forms.gle/b2B4wARBKUYjjrv98
E4C Guardians are our community moderators. You can ask them anything if you need help.
If you want to apply for the mod, plz fill in this form: https://forms.gle/6oJfRVJur5YitYVS8
E4C Commanders and Ambrus Studio Official. The two roles are team members from Ambrus Studio. The former is responsible for managing the community and serving all saviors in the communities. The latter will share some updates about E4C in some special events like deep-dive tea parties and AMAs.

About the E4C Rangers NFT
13. What is E4C Rangers NFT ?
E4C Rangers NFT is E4C鈥檚 first line of engagement with the community. The PFP project is derived from 7 characters in the E4Cverse and backed by strong utility including prosperous game rewards, lifetime discounts, and more in-game benefits.
In total, there are 4 tiers with different offerings of utility and a staking system allowing holders to upgrade their utility. Tiers are Ultimate, Gold, Rangers, and Hive.

14. What is the utility of Ultimate Edition?
The Ultimate Edition has the highest privilege. Its utility contains:
- $E4C governance token airdrop(Exact number TBA)
- Exclusive early access to the E4C games
- Ultimate Loot Box containing airdrops of in-game champions and skins
- 20% discount on in-game purchases
- Complementary gifts to 5 friends.

15. What is the utility of Gold Edition?
- $E4C governance token airdrop(Exact number TBA)
- Exclusive early access to the E4C games
- Gold Loot Box containing airdrops of in-game champions and skins
- 10% discount on in-game purchases
- Complementary gifts to 1 friend.

16. What is the utility of Rangers Edition?
- Rangers Loot Box containing airdrops of in-game champions and skins
- 5% discount on in-game purchases

17. What is the NFT upgrade system?
E4C Rangers are available to upgrade to the 鈥漃lus鈥 tier with advanced utility. The system requires NFT holders to stake their NFT on the E4C website for at least 35 days and get a special SBT badge. Please note that not all Rangers NFT are applicable to the upgrade system. Only Gold and Rangers can be upgraded.
Upgraded utility:
- From Gold to Gold+: Additional $E4C token airdrop(Exact number TBA), Gold+ Loot Box, 15% discount on in-game purchases, and complimentary gifts to 3 friends.
- From Rangers to Rangers+: $E4C token airdrop(Exact number TBA)锛 Gold Loot Box, 10% discount on in-game purchases, and complimentary gift to 1 friend.

18. What's the requirement for upgrading the NFT?
Stake the NFT for at least 35 days on the E4C website, during which time holders are also supposed to get a SBT badge called "Diamond hand" by completing a special community task.

19. What is the community task?
Holders should post a Tweet about his/her Rangers NFT and take a screenshot and send it to the #Tweets-done channel in our Discord and open a 鈥淒iamond hand registration鈥 ticket to submit his/her wallet address. The first time each holder manages to complete the community task, they鈥檒l receive a Diamond Hand SBT badge as an extra reward.

20. Can I withdraw my NFT during the staking period?
Yes. You can withdraw your NFT on our website at any time during the staking period. But once you withdraw it, your previous staking progress will be invalidated, and you must start over.

21. What is the lore of E4C Rangers?
The Amazon Rainforest is burning down, the Fuji mountain is erupting, the whole of Florida is underwater鈥
This is the year 2100, the world temperature has risen by 4鈩 due to environmental deterioration, causing the extinction of human races.
At that time, E4C Rangers emerge. The surviving humans establish a group named 鈥淩angers鈥 and struggle to survive on the remaining continent, hoping to find a piece of unpolluted land. Now, they are calling for all survivors to join the journey to salvation.
E4C Rangers are the first 7 characters coming to E4Cverse. They come from different backgrounds but they share the same faith, saving and rebooting the earth with their own hands.

22. When did the NFT project mint?
E4C Rangers NFT will be released in the sequence of 7 characters, with 1 character per batch. Up to now, we have 3 out of 7 minted, which are Heir of Musashi Rin, The Uncaged Reaper Kit, and Bumble Fighter Thorn. Rin and Kit are sold in three tiers (Ultimate-Gold-Rangers) and Thorn is a freemint collection with the Hive tier. You can find collections at OpenSea and Rarible.

23. How can users get access to the NFT mint?
We grant two groups of users with different privileges on minting time and minting price, the first group is E4Cverse Permit and the second group is Whitelist.

24. What is E4Cverse Permit?
E4Cverse Permit is the allowlist for the E4C Rangers NFT mint. Permit users are able to mint 48 hours before the public mint and enjoy 15% off the minting price. It is applicable for all the 7 Rangers.

25. How to get the E4Cverse Permit?
By collecting 5 community badges in the E4C Discord, users are available to get an E4Cverse Permit.

26. What is Whitelist?
Whitelist is the allowlist for the E4C Rangers NFT mint. Whitelist users are able to mint 24 hours before the public mint and enjoy 10% off the minting price. It is applicable for only one wave.

27. How to get the Whitelist?
By taking part in the community campaigns and winning the lucky draw, users can get the Whitelist with probability.

About the SBT badge system in the Discord community
28. What is the SBT badge?
E4C has designed a unique badge system deploying SBT to build an active and strong community in their E4Cverse.
Soulbound tokens are a new type of tokenized credential, identity, or affiliation. SBTs are non-transferable and non-financialized. Ethereum creator, Vitalik Buterin first introduced the idea along with E. Glen Weyl and Puja Ohlhaver, earlier this year.
The badge is the record of your achievement or contribution to the E4C community. It can also be considered proof of your identity in the E4C community. 

29. What is the utility of holding the badges?
We are continuously providing utilities to badge holders. Based on the number of collected badges, users can unlock utilities that will benefit the journey in E4Cverse, such as the E4Cverse Permit which grants users a discount on minting the E4C Rangers NFT.

30. How to get the SBT badges?
After you fulfill the specific requirements in our community, you will get the badge. You will be granted the related role in discord and later be airdropped the badge with SBTs.
